### ANNAPŪRṆA <span id="fr_385"></span>[1](#fn_385.md)

### (ANNAPŪRṆĀSTOTRA)

### FROM THE TANTRASĀRA <span id="fr_386"></span>[2](#fn_386.md)

1

SALUTATION to thee, O Devī!  
Dispenser of blessings, beloved of Śankara, <span
id="fr_387"></span>[3](#fn_387.md)  
Dear to devotees,  
Annapūrṇè.

2

Thou hast assumed form by *māyā* <span id="fr_388"></span>[4](#fn_388.md)  
Beloved of Śankara.  
Salutation to Maheśvarī, <span id="fr_389"></span>[5](#fn_389.md)  
O Annapūrṇé! obeisance to Thee. <span id="fr_390"></span>[6](#fn_390.md)

<span id="page_71">p. 71</span>

3

O Mahāmāyā! <span id="fr_391"></span>[1](#fn_391.md) beloved Spouse <span
id="fr_392"></span>[2](#fn_392.md) of Hara, <span
id="fr_393"></span>[3](#fn_393.md)  
Giver of the fruit of desire,  
Queen of *Suras*. <span id="fr_394"></span>[4](#fn_394.md)  
O Annapūrṇé! obeisance to Thee.

4

O Mahādevī with the lustre of a thousand rising suns,  
Three eyed,  
Crested with the crescent moon. <span id="fr_395"></span>[5](#fn_395.md)

5

O Devī! clad in fine garment,  
Ever giving rice, <span id="fr_396"></span>[6](#fn_396.md) Sinless One,  
Who delights in the dance of Śiva.  
Crested with the crescent moon. <span id="fr_397"></span>[5](#fn_395.md)  
O Annapūrṇé! obeisance to Thee.

6

O Devī! fulfiller of the desires of devotees, <span
id="fr_398"></span>[7](#fn_397.md)  
Destructress of worldly pain,  
Bending under the weight of Thy breasts. <span
id="fr_399"></span>[8](#fn_398.md)

<span id="page_72">p. 72</span>

O Annapūrṇé! obeisance to Thee.

7

Thou residest in the centre of the six-petalled lotus, <span
id="fr_400"></span>[1](#fn_399.md)  
And art in the form of the six-fold *śakti*, <span
id="fr_401"></span>[2](#fn_400.md)  
Thou art Brahmānī and all others, <span
id="fr_402"></span>[3](#fn_401.md)  
O Annapūrṇé! obeisance to Thee.

8

O Devī! adorned with crescent moon,  
All empires <span id="fr_403"></span>[4](#fn_402.md) are Thy gifts,  
Giver of delight to Sarva <span id="fr_404"></span>[5](#fn_403.md),  
O Annapūrṇé! obeisance to Thee.

9

Thy lotus feet are worshipped by Indra and other *Devās*;  
Thou assumest the form of Rudra and other *Devas*,  
Giver of wealth.  
O Annapūrṇé! obeisance to Thee.

<span id="page_73">p. 73</span>

10

Whoever <span id="fr_405"></span>[1](#fn_404.md) at time of worship  
Devoutly reads this hymn,  
In his house Lakṣmī <span id="fr_406"></span>[2](#fn_405.md) ever abides;  
True is this and without doubt.

11

Whoever having recited <span id="fr_407"></span>[3](#fn_406.md) the
*mantra* daily,  
Reads this hymn at dawn of day,  
Obtains wealth of rice  
And prosperity.

12

Not to all and any should this hymn be revealed,  
For be it made known to one who is unworthy,  
Then ills fall upon him,  
Therefore should it be carefully concealed.

